electrical tripping issue that troubled us for over three months. Several electricians came to diagnose it, but none were able to identify the root cause. Then we found Spark Electrician.\n\nAudre answered the phone and initially mentioned scheduling us later, but when he asked if this was an emergency and we explained how long the issue had been affecting us, he immediately said he would come personally. That already spoke volumes.\n\nAfter a brief introduction, Audre got straight to work, thoroughly inspecting wiring throughout the house. In a short time, he diagnosed the real issue: a previous contractor had incorrectly installed a light and wired it to another outlet, causing the tripping. Since then, the house has been working perfectly.\n\nAudre is calm, polite, and extremely professional. He only speaks when the information is useful, and every word matters. He explained that much of the electrical work in the house had been done poorly—wires not properly connected, screws not fully tightened—and helped us clearly understand what needed to be corrected. That’s when we decided to move forward with smart switches.\n\nAudre is confident and proactive. When I questioned whether certain things were even possible, he simply said, “Everything is possible, my friend.” That mindset instantly gave us confidence.\n\nThe next day, Audre provided a clear and detailed estimate after we shared the number of switches. Shortly after, Audre and his business partner Roman came fully prepared with smart switches. Within just two days, they transformed our large house into a fully smart home.\n\nTheir craftsmanship and attention to detail were outstanding. Every switch was installed perfectly. They moved furniture on their own, carefully checked every wire in every switch and outlet, and uncovered multiple issues left behind by previous electricians. They even installed a surge protector on the circuit board at no extra cost and surprised us with two remote controls as a gift.\n\