ervations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"103567629343368390765","name":"Pacific Peak Electric (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103567629343368390765"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Westgate","street":"22414 88th Ave W","city":"Edmonds","postal_code":"98026","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":null,"user_reviews":[{"Name":"kyle robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZH7lipAZkX9KRCtx1G9nCRrw2YU04XiarJq6gGihU-82CfrkL=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the moment I spoke with Steve he was extremely kind and informative! He's a great communicator and got me the quote when he said he would and the price was great compared to other options out there. Not to mention he was generous enough to fit us into his busy schedule!\n\nOn the day of install he was at our home early and got the job done seamlessly! He was quick to follow up with me to help answer any questions I had regarding the work that was done.\n\nSteve and Pacific Peak Electric are a stand up team and I will be using them for all electrical work in the future and highly recommend you do as well!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sean MacLean","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOQCNk9uHhEzDuN1deEb6lDWywhcu1GpDfIS7rdneO5qWaApSs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great communicators in an age of vanishing accountability!\nFor my hot tub subpanel installation, owner Steve Kopta was not only quick to respond, but asked for just the right details in order to create a contract.\nIt's so nice to step into a project with clear expectations.  When a misprint from the hot tub company required a pivot in their installation plans, Steve and his team adjusted graciously, despite the inconvenience to them. Their work was aesthetic, clean, totally pro. They were polite and unharried.  The presence was total, not like some contractors whom you feel are rushing through to get to the next job.  I recommend them without hesitation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alyssa Samuelson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSog6TX0UmitA6-zJRiyRuIpaXUsL6Eugl1cedUSV10ox5VA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steve and his team are the best. They were super thorough, made really helpful recommendations, took on more work than originally planned, and were great communicators. Steve regularly checked in and kept us updated throughout the project and was invested in a happy outcome. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leah Vitcovich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3p9PZQBTV95iKY70QDYCCZ8ZvpzU96ESasadsSpUzGczwpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steve \u0026 Josh provided excellent service to quickly resolve an intermittent but persistent GFI overload problem for us.  They were fantastic at diagnosing what was going on, explaining the solution and then efficiently performing repairs with both professionalism and confidence. Pacific Peak has a well organized website with an easy-to-use online tool to contact them, and we were very impressed with how quickly they responded and got us on their schedule.  I would not hesitate for a second to contact them for future electrical work or recommend them to friends and family! On top of our delight at getting things fixed, we were pleasantly surprised at how reasonable the fee was.   Really quality care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Roy Baccellieri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIKjaKmhPy70lAy9Z11MAzkLMjhaXfrT626nJnCeuxbyYcVvMwC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had such a great experience working with Pacific Peak Electric. Steve and his crew are the best! Their communication and attention to detail were top notch. I would definitely use them in the future and highly recommend using them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hannah Han","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVx37J4B-DPxnys0Er43V59pbmbqR318kBX8rPl5FDMlgQAcLFh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently worked with Steve and his team to update our electrical system in the kitchen to replace gas stove to induction, and we were so happy with the quality of work and such great communication all throughout. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Holly Bates","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcswRJzr0FktzL_Bo7mbXGqcz0f2pL0xrTneJDBfyFFyJzZYp1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Do you ever get the feeling that good help is hard to find lately? The number of emails and messages I’ve sent lately to folks for work done around our new house, only to get no response (or to get ghosted), is pretty wild.\n\nSo it was a real pleasure to get a prompt message and quote from Steve for the electrical work we needed. He had guys at our house about 48 hours later, and they were courteous, efficient and clean! Very pleased with the quality, and relieved to know we have a company we can count on when future projects arise.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Gillis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe6V54feuJUkO9FEv9s1PIYw7Ea6gH1c57MYJUZpeAu-JMogjT=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In 2017 we bought a house built in the 1920s that had undergone a few partial-remodels leaving the electrical systems a mixture of old and new. Last month our lights and appliances started dimming and losing power intermittently. We knew we needed to address the old knob-and-tube and a 100amp panel that was most likely too small for the house - but our immediate concern was fixing the flickering and outages. We ended up having four different electrical companies come out to take a look - and all but one company seemed pre-occupied with winning the \"big job\" (upgrading everything in the house) instead of fixing the immediate issue. That one company was Pacific Peak Electrical. They sent out two electricians (with tools) ready to find and (if authorized) fix the problem. They found the problem in about 10 mins and had it fixed within a few hours. They then gave us estimates on additional work. Needless to say, we’ve found “our electricians” and will be using Pacific Peak Electric for all additional work.\nJim and Stephanie Gillis. NE Seattle","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
