googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVLKPYVpfWiXf0FFLJiI4ewWquBiV9KgO9iqUuJsW8xs7_pA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Levi showed up right on time and did a fantastic job! Our home in Burien is nearly a century old, and he really understood how to work with the older wiring and made sure everything was upgraded for safety. He worked quickly and was able to rewire three ceiling fans and light fixtures in just a few hours. The price was much less than I expected, which was a pleasant surprise. From now on, we’ll definitely call them for any electrical work, and I’m already telling my neighbors about this great service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Judith Flores","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdd3pibZh2Y5TVaZspOaRVdMN2pV4Hb2n7U2xE17NJNl6X7A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Seattle Rapid Neighborhood Electricians is truly the best electrical company I’ve worked with! I needed to have an old Federal Pacific electrical panel replaced in my new house in Burien. Since it’s a big project, I got a few quotes first. One company tried to charge me $14,000 and claimed I needed all my main wiring replaced and that my smoke detectors had to be hardwired, which wasn’t true. After that, I contacted Seattle Rapid Neighborhood Electricians and had Melvin come out. He was very skilled and took care of everything quickly and safely. The electrical inspector signed off on the work, and I was happy to find out my smoke detectors could just be battery operated. The whole job, including the permit, was only $2,500. Everyone I spoke to was friendly and professional. I am so grateful for their honest advice, great service, and fair prices. Highly recommend if you need an electrician in Burien!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michaela7 M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKaURzsj30QMlTLalz-ttnb5EM29w32nmL08BiuuxlfuH5LsA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"everyone we interacted with was friendly and 