ate was fast, the work was scheduled without any complexity, and the team showed up right on time.\n\nThe work was done really well, very tidy, very complete. I had several aspects to the overall project — new panel, hot tub circuit, more circuits for water heater and dryer — and I’m really happy with it. They did a very professional job, I asked for a modification to run some wires through joists and it was not a problem. They were friendly and professional, and had a good plan to get the work done and minimize the electricity being off.\n\nThe inspector said they did a very good job and he had seen their work before so wasn’t surprised. It looked good, and they corrected something with the grounding too. I would absolutely recommend Mogovolt and will call them again for my next project!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicole Faghin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGJANfE-8JyzNnc3zhx3lf_nFoZcZ25Vx9CO2hZPnteIL-eIqr5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Daniel and the whole Mogovolt team were very responsive and communicated extremely well. They installed new pathway lighting and a new electrical box as well as an ev charging station for us. In all aspects of their work they were very efficient and diligent. We would highly recommend them for electrical work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sam Veatch","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXj1ayNtMLga4-T4dW01VwTprZsTkaZVxuzzp2CMVNMncp064=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Mogovolt team were fantastic! They provided a fair quote, did quick (and fastidiously clean) work, and made thoughtful recommendations while onsite performing the work. I would strongly recommend and will be hiring them when I need electrical work done in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Theodore Furr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhbH0SDfJ-L7jF0x3XLLaJDfbZvt6BtulOCktZyV3e56XD1XI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to schedule, arrived on time, did great work, easy to coordinate with.  Professional and patient with EV installation and set up.  Answered questions and stayed until confirmed that everything worked properly.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tanner Lyons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwenO82XHOuB5jyAiMGNKVU3Yzv7js-VV1nsZRHLCL-14GSvc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If I could give Mogovolt a 6-star rating, I absolutely would. Before becoming a General Contractor, I spent several years working alongside them as a Project Manager for different company on countless home remodels—and their work consistently speaks for itself.\n\nFor the past six years, they’ve been my go-to electrical team on every single project I’ve managed or been a part of. They’re always punctual, efficient, incredibly hard-working, and their work passes inspection flawlessly every single time.\n\nWhen I started managing my own projects as a GC, I knew I needed an electrical partner who shared my values of honesty, integrity, and uncompromising quality. With Mogovolt, I found exactly that—and I’ve never once looked back.\n\nI would highly recommend Mogovolt for your next project!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amelia Hertog","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUefrd9wbCf8OQsB8q12-yer8IrgVD_fgaSzAP_MiN1HhS6Aqs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve hired Mogovolt Electrical for two new build homes, and Daniel and his team have been exceptional every time. They deliver top-quality electrical work, are trustworthy, professional, and great communicators, and their pricing is fair and transparent.\nIf you’re searching for a reliable residential electrician or electrical contractor near me, look no further. Mogovolt shows up on time, keeps you informed, and gets the job done right the first time. They’re creative, efficient, and easy to work with, which makes every project stress-free.I confidently recommend Mogovolt to all my family, friends, and real estate clients because they consistently provide outstanding service, excellent workmanship, and true peace of mind.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate Koeppel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUK7G3NHpq4pK60FReqWUfk1dZ_sM22LeAWOGB3stQuBUXon5Ia-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hired Mogovolt to replace all knob and tube wiring in our 100 year old home in Queen Anne and update all outlets and switches with new brass hardware. Additionally, we upgraded our overhead service to 200 amps and installed a new larger panel and hardwired all smoke and CO detectors.\n\nI got quotes from a number of local companies, and while all were close in their pricing, Mogovolt’s came in a bit lower, with a number of very strong referrals from neighbors, as well as Homeowner’s Club.\n\nThis project ended up being a more complicated project than we anticipated, because old houses have secrets- ours happened to have a lot more active knob and tube than we had originally anticipated when we bought the house. The Mogovolt team from start to finish was incredibly detailed in their estimates, explanations and ideas for updating our wiring with not just solutions that we liked, but were well-thought through, up to code aligned with new building standards. Communication was outstanding- even when I didn’t understand something they took the time to explain different decisions and possible solutions.\n\nThe team was incredibly polite, tidy and thoughtful in our home. Adi and Ben were always very communicative and gave us great morning and end of day updates- additionally they were happy to talk through solutions and explain, and reexplain more than once a number of tricky decisions we had to think through and understand. The whole team is clearly very experienced, detail-oriented and extremely professional, they kept each of their work areas clean and organized daily. I would not hesitate to hire them again for any electrical work big or small. This was a huge job and put so much effort in from the beginning to end, I really can’t recommend them enough.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"893a08a5-609b-4514-b314-e8085a1c0abf","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/OHM+Electrical+Contracting/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x549041061548f1af:0xc8ece2e5fdd99f2c!8m2!3d47.5521581!4d-122.3257811!16s%2Fg%2F11ff0x2zvl!19sChIJr_FIFQZBkFQRLJ_Z_eXi7Mg?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"14478196379523587884","title":"OHM Electrical Contracting","categories":["Electrician","Electrical installation service"],"category":"Electrician","address":"620 S Orcas St Suite 80127, Seattle, WA 98108","open_hours":{"Friday":["7 AM–4 PM"],"Monday":["7 AM–4 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["7 AM–4 PM"],"Tuesday":["7 AM–4 PM"],"Wednesday":["7 AM–4 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"https://ohmelectricalcontracting.com/","phone":"(206) 973-9184","plus_code":"HM2F+VM Seattle, Washington","review_count":9,"review_rating":4.6,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":1,"2":0,"3":0,"4":0,"5":8},"latitude":47.5521581,"longtitude":-122.3257811,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHqojrveboJgwQoPQk_ftwEwcSytiszBW95ZEpeh8dLmZnZIxiA6cSasqQ7z2JaTfmsq0oedtYvlzMrfi0qza7ID-BbTTm_4uXJyip9njkXuGCGexU8IbDQjYUfL_Rw8Xno5KX5=w408-h272-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x549041061548f1af:0xc8ece2e5fdd99f2c","place_id":"ChIJr_FIFQZBkFQRLJ_Z_eXi7Mg","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHqojrveboJgwQoPQk_ftwEwcSytiszBW95ZEpeh8dLmZnZIxiA6cSasqQ7z2JaTfmsq0oedtYvlzMrfi0qza7ID-BbTTm_4uXJyip9njkXuGCGexU8IbDQjYUfL_Rw8Xno5KX5=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHwwXKe4YM0J0mbNKPuiaeCJLvcbVn-W8-WyzFtYuU49I6HWwyHpAkPjEbm3LBA_ChE87QMUunhPdYHuvx8nZEUBhLR_3aymUwhZkvxzqqb7-MR5Hu8zsVs7A7OWj3m1IaZjqaMww=w446-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Videos","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAG2Os4GtVyvq2ZCXOLSv6F0CkCAJ2I3Fv_3Bppb46wcV2XJKghJggwAOMtkiIQsaPY5ikRJJLfN6Cpt97TjDFJ6aTWF-prDH__jWXm9p6WUeVjtAjYOOTIDkLdUxlGwsLJMRE8kng=w397-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=MF7mfyLnaQha75JHvgTwvw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=10.763083\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"103885283797120110937","name":"OHM Electrical Contracting (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103885283797120110937"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Georgetown","street":"620 S Orcas St Suite 80127","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98108","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Massimo Gatti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK_TLKcgS6HShKfssBWM4HsyNxTz802K2aLPcTPe0gBmt-e-Pb7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing work, definitely recommended!\n\nI had a lot of work to be done to an old house with an old panel:\n-new 200 Amps panel\n-level 2 EV charger\n-home surge protection\n-generator plug outdoor with interlock in main panel\n-heat pump hook up\n\nAlfred stopped by quick, did a free consultation and estimate, answered all my questions via email in details, for a few days we discussed all the details and he provided different options with associated datasheets. (I'm a really picky customer :) ).\n\nHe recommended me to get an EV charger level 2 to take advantage of the rebate ending in February, I was not even aware of that.\n\nHe also worked with the city seamlessly and in a timely fashion. When the work was scheduled, his team showed up and in a day they did all the work without any assistance.\n\nThe whole installation looks great, the team has great attention to details and they have been really accommodating my asks.\n\nGreat job Alfred and Ohm Electrical team!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthony Morales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURPyGREuTbNQBzk_gbduxSI8b7QhdAMnoK2ZoKijdvDPANfHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After installing new siding on our home, we had an issue where a circuit breaker would constantly trip. This left us with no power to 1.5 of our 3 bedrooms. Within 48hrs, OHM was able to come on-site (free) and produce a quote to troubleshoot the issue. Not only did they provide the most detailed estimate of the contractors we had come on-site, Alfred also greatly impressed us with his willingness to explain the process and answer any questions.\n\nA week later, we had Chris and Justin at our house performing the troubleshooting. Just like with Alfred, they were on time, extremely polite/professional, and very responsive to all of our questions, including some that extended beyond the current issue at hand. Alfred also stopped by halfway through the service call and was able to give us an impromptu walk-through of potential additional options to address a separate, underlying concern Chris and Justin had found. However, Alfred was also very pragmatic in making sure we didn't take on unnecessary cost/work as he actively sought to understand what our actual needs/goals would be in order to determine if the additional work was necessary. Oh, and did I fail to mention they found the issue and fixed it in the same visit, not causing us to incur any additional charges from the troubleshooting quote (aside from materials)? =)\n\nOverall, they were great, well priced, and very customer-centric. If/when we have any future electrician needs, we will be reaching back out to OHM and happily recommending them to others.\n\n*NOTE: Our home is from the '40s with a LOT of \"unique electrical design choices\" that OHM had to overcome, further adding value to the service they provided!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Darcey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVsG9isIdyYUbfp5I-kXWmfmU22VggnquHX4Y8gbN-aPgfv-Jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I could not be happier with my experience working with Ohm Electrical.  I had a pretty massive knob \u0026 tube wire removal project for my home and they:\n\n- came in with a bid that was HALF the cost of the two other bids i received\n- completed the work exactly on time and at a high quality\n- ended up costing even less b/c they identified work in the original bid that wasn't ultimately required\n- communicated well the entire time\n\nI also requested a quote a while back for my kitchen remodel and really wanted to go with Ohm Electrical but the general contractor I hired recommended his own guy.  I regret not pushing to go with Ohm on that one!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"RJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFXYJPKnQvLBWWuwdb7YiK_REVxqhAnlgJk9Tq06rpOXvvMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So in spite of the fact that OHM electric overcharged for invoices the last time we hired them and we finally had to call to get them to straightened out the matter before paying, against my better judgement I hired Ohm again.  I will say Alfred is a fairly competent electrician but Ian the guy who books the appointments and does the billing proved to be an absolutely nightmare, who can not be trusted with the truth. Please note that fact in that any response to this review by Ian will  certainly be a misrepresentation .\n\nSo I scheduled the service at my address on line through their web site and then by calling. Both times I gave him my address and confirmed it.  Then the night before they were suppose to come, all of a sudden he sends a text to my son, cancelling the appointment, because he alleges that we did not confirm the address for yet again, a third time,!\n\nApparently Ian sent an email which I did not notice wanting a third confirmation  He triumphantly cancelled the appointment, even though he could have just taken the time to text or call to confirm the address if he still had doubts. Well we took off that morning to await them at the project and suddenly we got noticed that they was not going to show up. I feel like charging him for my time,\n\nWhen I complained about his sudden cancellation, he told me I was unprofessional! Now that is an oxymoron if anything not only because all the unprofessional behavior was on the part of Ian whose tone was increasingly arrogant but the fact that he was the professional doing the business, and I was simply a customer who had given him all the contact info he needed if he had any questions,\n\nSo after unprofessionally cancelling the service on a whim, I decided never ever to use this company again, a fact I conveyed to them in no uncertain terms. There are in fact lots of other professional electricians that show up on time and don't try to shift the blame on to the customer after mistakes of their own making!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Meryl McQueen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc1LsjLJunZoQJt6Oug8AM-Mt63rJHsSfUkAhcKoHfFA-WQ9Sykg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"OHM Electrical has been a pleasure to work with. From my first contact with Ian and quote visit with Alfred through to efficient, professional work completed more quickly than expected by Giuseppe and Justin, I highly recommend this fantastic team. They were able to answer my questions and offer a terrific solution for my project.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabrielle Oglesby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXbPtCFuqjWLA9lnsNRWf3Q9i4vxkrGqCh_LscMag3wVHOmMlV_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I live in a vintage camper trailer with dated and poorly done wiring. I called after one of my lines stopped working. Alfred quickly diagnosed and repaired the issues, while also providing useful electrical information.","Images":null,"When":""},{