https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111564982895672702442"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Seattle Chinatown-International District","street":"515 7th Ave S","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98104","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Fibonacci Love","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKxK4yI0jnETsoIP9kpHQliKQusO8tW1qm3NsICOubuf34U6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Giovanni, Josh, and McCoy did an outstanding job! They first helped me with a simple issue under my bathroom sink after I got completely stuck trying to reinstall the pipes — the gaskets wouldn’t fit and I had accidentally thrown away a couple of parts. They fixed everything quickly and professionally.I also had them look at my water heater, which had been installed incorrectly by someone else. They immediately identified several serious problems, explained what was wrong, and came back the very next day to repair it properly.The improvements were immediate: stronger water pressure, smooth and consistent water flow, and a correctly installed gas line that finally makes me feel safe.These guys are knowledgeable, honest, and extremely skilled. I highly recommend them for any plumbing work!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2LYy0KlQZm7G23SZgkrMB8wHoXGT1qw7aB5Nr2o2SYWEWhVtb4wg3V4SHnZCG_2VE4H8izu43IS3a7RILINhAwArIhzuyMrcOBc-Y2eqrsaAtIKsV3BFatUgxmnKWBEbLCY4SCu1UG2HBo=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1gl8S0Vdg597_a6QrBjgnXImSN7fWCmU23hDs28R1uhkcuZOqsL7CGYfTBYoRbc-RHeYvlsWm9_jb4nw4C8LfKX_0xBo1Jn3yq4w5dzClaAA3OJRTU-0scFZUE3D6cAX0jdRenMOvMeyg=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-28"},{"Name":"Eunique Washington","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVg959PBKoGmOcgFKNNfNODQpzySIS-qH2DIqxNKhOF77EZw1vl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had such a great experience with Diontea! He arrived promptly to handle our toilet repair and drain cleaning quickly and efficiently. He was super friendly, informative, and genuinely kind throughout the entire process. He took the time to explain what was going on and made sure we felt comfortable with everything before moving forward.\n\nOn top of that, his pricing was very fair and reasonable. It’s hard to find someone trustworthy and thorough these days, and we’re so grateful we found him. Highly recommend!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordyn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlQVRLVxN6Zi9xJptVZhyAEr2KbMb-q1c4BWaeVd6GKElchw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time using Beacon Plumbing, Heating, Electrical \u0026 Mechanical for HVAC work. After a few great experiences with their plumbing teams in late 2024, we figured we'd give them a try. Happy to say it was a good choice!\n\nHuge thanks to Ian + Damon for coming out this week to install a new furnace. After giving them the rundown of some troubleshooting steps we'd taken on our own, Ian + Damon talked us through the diagnostic tests they were running before outlining the way forward: replacing a potentially hard-to-source circuit board vs. installing a new furnace, work timelines, price ranges, etc. Since our existing furnace was ~28 years old, we took Ian + Damon's recommendation to install a new one. We were pleasantly surprised by how quickly this all came together. The diagnostic, removal, furnace delivery + installation were all done in a matter of 2-3 hours.\n\nIan + Damon were kind and communicative throughout the whole process. We genuinely felt comfortable asking questions and appreciated their thoughtful + patient responses. Needless to say, we'd be happy to work with Ian, Damon + Beacon Plumbing again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kendra Greenwood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNuLwrJvc5fK3iCMGLrodMLhnkrpC8WicD7uIKlAg9PSJSGiFKGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jesus and Alfredo did a wonderful and efficient job moving a natural gas line for us. They came within 24hrs for a quote and then the following day to fix the issue. They gave us a fair price, quite a bit less than our other quote. The other thing I loved about Jesus and Alfredo is that they introduced themselves to my contractor who was working. Of the two others who came to give quotes, no one else introduced or acknowledged my contractor. Thanks for being professional, kind, timely, and excellent!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2o7TSiZLqS4f7BQQ2gDHfuwBxtyOkPFhssjsN1kEQseaxEU7wBHgkqfEz4ciL400D4BySYeaLHO-ugXJANm7Xy2McccVd6BqV1ejnEttCNHxHlKAt04FdbdP4YJChHXMo28ml1T_OlNkM=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-11"},{"Name":"Andrew Hughes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXu77kJi3QUn23OKE0B8Nej99uH41smFj3mAH_qJarvD_engcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beacon Plumbing once again proved why they’re my first call without hesitation. Tony and Victor were outstanding today while servicing our heat pump — professional, knowledgeable, and incredibly thorough. Not only did they perform excellent maintenance, but they quickly assessed and identified a crucial repair that finally solved a mystery issue we’ve been dealing with for months.\n\nThey took the time to clearly explain what was happening, what was needed, and why — communication was excellent from start to finish. The repairs were completed quickly, efficiently, and at a competitive price, exactly what I’ve come to expect from Beacon. They even went above and beyond by reattaching insulation that had fallen down around the heat pump, which was greatly appreciated.\n\nThe quality of work, kindness of the individuals who represent Beacon, and the trust that they’ll always do the right thing at the best price is why I continue to call them time and again. Huge thanks to Tony, Victor, and the entire Beacon team for another exceptional experience.\n\nHighly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeffrey Toews","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFHrT7GePyv-xPmGNwMM0VY9nsSnOP9BjgzxkKR700gqdMMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had great experience with Ian and Damon, who came out to assess our 11+ year old Mitsubishi HVAC units. They demonstrated solid technical product knowledge of the units and, coupled with their experience maintaining and replacing many other units around Seattle, helped lay out options for us. Given the age of our HVAC units \u0026 condensors and the cost \u0026 effort of a full internal clean/refurbish, we opted to go with upgrading them to new units. They walked me through the somewhat involved process of installing the new system, clearly breaking down the different stages, asking important clarifying questions giving me confidence that they were invested in an outcome that would align with both the design of our house and how we use it. Am looking forward to moving ahead and partnering with them on this upgrade once I get the full proposal. Additionally, while on site, they took the time to look at our plumbing, specifically our new tankless water heater that another company had installed, and - based on my mention of a previous flood caused by my old water heater - recommended and professionally installed a new flood protection system that will automatically shut off the water supply the moment a leak is detected. Ian and Damon solidly represent Beacon Plumbing and were a total pleasure to work with!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Aylen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIA5gun-JvrLzkxJS6IaPganmYZVUIrAgWiAtYgdVy7K5MUQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an issue with no hot water circulating that we noticed Friday night and called on a Saturday morning at 7 am. Someone answered and scheduled techs to come out that morning! Ian and Damon were extremely courteous, knowledgeable, professional and organized. They were at our house for 6 hours installing the new tanks and went over everything at the end on how to use and care for it. They were very personable and kind and we cannot thank them enough for getting us hot water again over the weekend with out of town guests coming that night! We had a great experience using Beacon plumbing! Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C Fuda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVOMV-J_IIX_ViGzu5OeVON491MuK5amLVPznmLQ8FWymbeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I confidently endorse my experience with Beacon Plumbing. Upon arrival, Jeremy and David promptly addressed the issue. I was installing a new shower, and they quickly identified a problem with the drain. They diagnosed and resolved the issue efficiently. Throughout the process, they clearly explained each step, and everything was transparently listed on my invoice. Their customer service was impeccable. The most important thing is that they earned my trust after past plumbing experiences with other companies were a nightmare. I won’t have to worry anymore. I’ll call Beacon plumbing.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
