ns":[{"name":"Installation service","enabled":true},{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Norman Zyskowski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLULL1Qpai13YcIs6ca5wwbuAHGx-0axaY3ffLrcSuvEkAWmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I needed a furnace check-up/ tune up.\nThe technician Daniel showed up on time with an awesome attitude.\nVery considerate about our surroundings.\nAnd went right to work.\nHe found some things that needed attention explained to me what they were showed me a part that needed replaced gave me the cost of the part and asked me if I wanted it replaced.\nDaniel did all the work cleaned up and was done in no time..\nHe let me know my furnace was in good shape.\nVery professional .\nI would use Brennan again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKic6nbbJWaFkS4nRjwZGpHEIQwMMFq8mpGBbGdy7YwG100WA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"On one of the coldest days of the year our furnace malfunctioned. Brennan responded right away and got the furnace fixed same day.  The technician, Ibs, was punctual, courteous, clear in explaining the problem and fixed the problem. Thanks for the great work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly Bryant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAw6XcSDk3EktAC6wpS06JkxM4VaO48xIZKlJzLENIm2-m7xzc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"READ BEFORE DOING BUSINESS WITH BRENNAN!\n\nThis is a review that started 11 years ago. I was in need of a more efficient heating system. Costco had a Brennan rep at the exit. I spoke with them and I ended up with a Lennox mini split installed for $6400. Everything was great. Fast forward 11 years, the outside unit failed at the coldest time of the year. I called Brennan and they sent out a tech. I was told the unit was dead and parts were no longer available. I was quoted $11400 for a lower quality system! Even with cost increases over the years, double seemed excessive.\n\nI had another tech from another company out. He told me $300 to install a new control board but it was possible there was a short that would fry the new board instantly. With further inspection, that tech found that the needed 4-wire bundle from the outside unit to the head unit was actually a 3-wire with no actual ground wire. Instead an 8 inch wire with a striped end on both ends that used the metal interior of the conduit as a jumper was used as the ground wire (See photo). The new tech told me this is most likely what caused the failure and was an improper installation. And if the permit inspector had known that's what was done, they would have never sign-off on the installation.\n\nI found a more affordable option and finally have heat again. I attempted multiple times to contact Brennan to let them known about what was found. I finally spoke with a supervisor after leaving several unreturned voice mails. I told him the situation and he basically said, it passed inspection and they wouldn't do anything about it. I told him I still have the old unit and wire to show them the problem. He said it's been too long and again that it passed inspection. I asked him if they would at least haul away the old unit because refrigerant requires a specific disposal process. The supervisor agreed to email me after he spoke with the owner. It's been months and I have received no emails or phone calls.\n\nBe warned, Brennan takes short cuts and does improper (if not illegal) installations. If you have any equipment installations done by them, speak directly to the permit inspector before they sign-off on the permit. Don't let their short cuts cost you thousands later on.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2mjcw7asTYqo5CeDHVp_1ZAwIXD9wXDs2E-X09Il-G9HokVomqEbG3ZM09i4UykuXdlVU_yWn5OvUWsO_D_jFJQdHyF8jGAaMCzgNpoBXdTIVoa5LSA9pBB5lZvM_VPfarj0zodqUVPg11=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-16"},{"Name":"Jc C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVfFowbI9JwnJ6fbYH3Nt6Rfcsnc1i2fq9N5TO0UjZe2Q71ruW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Brennan heating install my Heat pump and furniture.from Costco.  Dakota service rep came and service my unit. At that to time we discussed my concerns about the lack of flow to a particular section of my house.  He went underneath my house and said that the duct needs to reroute . He said that he would work up a quote and get back to me.  Several weeks goes by and I haven't heard from Dakota so I called Brennan and they told me they have to speak with Dakota I never received a call. Several  months has passed.  I called Brennan and they again told me they would call me back with a quote.  Twice they have said they would call me back and never followed through.  Brennan Im sure Costco wouldn't be happy with the way you are treating their customers.  Don't worry about contacting me I will take my business somewhere else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Mertlich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7lYdRtapl0Umptd-Hns6eB8RAV7taI1XksGeblBTfHMc6uD85=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We chose Brennan Heating through Costco and paid several thousand dollars more specifically for the higher level of customer service we were promised, but the experience has been the opposite. The installation was left incomplete, multiple technicians failed to fix issues leaving us with no heat and the communication throughout the process was extremely poor. The salesperson who introduced himself as our project manager repeatedly promised phone calls he never made, and at one point even told me he was “equally frustrated,” which was incredibly upsetting given that he was supposed to be managing our project—not commiserating. We also dealt with miscommunication about a scheduled duct test and repeated scheduling issues that required family members to drop everything to let technicians in. After paying over $22,000, the lack of professionalism, accountability, and follow-through has been extremely disappointing and far below what Costco customers are led to expect.\n\nAfter repeated attempts to get someone to contact me to resolve our issues we felt we need to share our experience in an effort to prevent others from dealing with this.  I will be sharing all details with Costco as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ahmad Yaghoobi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXTiNZjR5N_uWa5Xk6e6_LtGGWQ46aHBhEKXoWSOcQ6xndhfk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ibrahima did a great job servicing our fur as. He was on-time and ready to go. Ibrahima was very knowledgeable, helpful, and above all very respectful and friendly! I specially appreciate his workmanship and dedication! Thanks Ibrahima!\n\nKind regards,\nAhmad","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lynne Castle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuL141p6Q-hqESxHcfmDA-RUnxPg3ievtQS_K6Gj-bKunPbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Brad from Brennan was great.  He went through our old furnace and said it is in good shape.  He explained what possibly caused it to stop and restart in a few hours and that there is 'No Need to Replace' it.   Best service on the planet!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J Douglas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXv2Kciyd-izbTYjNWh6T_h1bRYE81VaSB-e6CU68YnTzGtiEcvIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience with Brennan installing our new mini-split, ductless heat-pump/AC system. Went through Costco so we also got 10 percent back in the form a cash card.  Paul, our sales person came out and recommended a 2.5 ton system for our log cabin - he didn't over sell us on a bigger system like 2 other HVAC  companies tried to do with their bids.  Also, the Brennan bid came in way less than the other two (do your diligence and get 2-3 bids is what my Dad taught me). The crew that came out to install was also top-notch and super friendly, I highly recommend Brennan for their service, professionalism, value and quality of equipment they sell.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2oNJLl-RrHVuGg2XwJZUQg-bcLwkYWp5KPBasbhMj1YNn4ry68McsYrZLP1zOSwzoaOqsnMqXZ1SdAdQrsTobPPk4VBjHM8mQqIZPpZv8TnWkvKTRB_cV9AxIjTFcC86y-mRA-=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0QXeJKAiprI-VhUG3zwVhykJyEfIRJCk9XGrVtGX8qyR3BbR4NVTB0r1Xep-qoV00kx27u0_UuE_ZTGZT3cHRdFQ06W_Ou-zET_REJdgn8S1QILc73w2kClolz1bSjXZ32ukJVYg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3qCW8djrIAdkUf5ci4HSNIuXORWeQ3XQQnHciwYyh6y1mhIknFo4mIMhPq8JGhRWr82GbZ49o2P9WWH2jcKNR6rL8qX0iG67ryew_aqEdaNlWma9eQCscKjk6RQ-cCBifD41Uo=k-no"],"When":"2023-6-7"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
