dow. The electricians and the office folks communicated well and thoroughly, worked quietly and efficiently, and quoted accurately.  They also did a great job cleaning up after themselves.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2R-x71p6CgY9R9zESdNWam-2qIxhbQzAiGMQWyGT4jmy8s-ELjSzDvadUpWYuRh3sPVu-0MW4CLpWqg2lqaupoZwNdyiKVYZPTfRLYV4jdcdUz73FgtCLqjL9k80FKIuDQE0QS=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2c8bFc2AE0YS_B8JrArbD1rokleM1LV3W1R3xa1afIJyzVwXra27jjAeuS1csNvym4f0FAEdumXOGGfTVtRDSSUg92MFHpGBE6axv1Ali6RuaLJuBfHwrllnYSd7VgiOjwguXkLw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn124HVHKsykhcfU6bqMtnjxsU_XARepwVUHssGUmIC_8Y_n6NYb7jFKUTmzISndjfMYhALUt9mR2kGzqlDET4JHeOur-IfLjiK2wbnx8pmUSuTrEKHtwMnPeHDV2Nu5Qdnf-Hnp=k-no"],"When":"2024-7-10"},{"Name":"Gabriel Aurioles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeNiO6SwzIstKpOKAGAH1b7LHylf9a09zcELJW1SmEsnh2a38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 stars but beware: VERY EXPENSIVE, especially when paired with a third party intermediary like Electrum/Genesis.  I have an EV charger installed and their quote was ~$500 MORE than all other quotes from licensed electricians.  I thought I was getting a good deal the fist offer from Electrum/Genesis but then the actual quote was a lot more!!!.  Oh well...Just bewar!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Linnea R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwO4OPOZ-tESzNFexx-_C_LjAktI94UxoBIaL2vWMvW0Z3rhQH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome experience.  I worked with several people at Custom Electrical Services who all contributed to this being a success.  Of course when you get bids it's easy to pick the lowest number, but there are so many other factors to consider.\n\nCost:  I got three bids and they offered me the most competitive price.  So that’s a good start.\n\nReliability and Timing:  These guys showed up on time and ended on time.  They committed the resources to make sure the job got done.  Kyle was finishing the job and when he left, he had taken care of every last detail.\n\nExpertise: Luis was managing the job at my house and he is INCREDIBLE.  He is smart and has so much experience.  He came with fresh ideas and advice I had never considered, and helped me craft the most perfect lighting plan for my house.\n\nFlexibility: I decided on some changes mid-way through and it was really critical to work with a company that was happy to accommodate these.\n\nQuality of Work:  Their work is beautiful.  Tidy and thoughtful.  No random damage and problems that you’ll find with other contractors.  The wiring is clean, and they consider every detail.   They also take the time to show you your options and not just assume things.\n\nCommunication: Excellent across the board.  Josh was great in coordinating the job and checking in. Luis kept me informed at every step along the way.  Also, between phases and I had a bunch of time-sensitive questions that came up and he responded to me instantly!  Luis is an angel an went way above and beyond.  Kyle also had great communication; he even let me know right away when some other contractors showed up at my house unbeknownst to me…  I am so thankful Kyle was looking out for me and my house.\n\nOverall Experience:  I’m simply grateful.  This project could have easily been a disaster since I needed so much guidance, but they were thoughtful and patient and took the time to make sure my dream became a reality.  Their customer service is awesome and it is so clear that these guys are extremely trustworthy and they just CARE.  It goes a long way.\n\nHere's a picture of my new kitchen lighting.  The rest is still under construction but you get the general idea :)","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Me34onj5ZTffIGqRVA_hVOY0HtZNk3w3ZpQJzEEdNhmc1MRQUhyFrzoXWYjulvWInay2Z8csS0vsWRgjc9V5auUGthlkWMqeMMiXbOaCEeLYhZbb9UEozlWFQvCOwj0PijtojyA=k-no"],"When":"2017-11-5"}],"us