 not been replaced since we got the generator nearly 10 years ago. All in all I truly reasonable price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chuck Malmsten","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjL1LxxlWlMADfsWyZZZIJEEK8lVkvJqakIl3J_C_-thL0iuA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bryan, Tyler (and a 3rd electrician, sorry, I forgot his name) installed an Ecoflow Smart Home Panel 2, part of a whole house battery backup system. They arrived on time, had all the parts and tools they needed. They appreciated the diagrams I provided identifying the circuits (18) to be moved to the new sub-panel transfer switch. They evaluated the work area, came up with an installation plan, and got to work. They completed the job sooner than expected, tested the system, cleaned up, and labeled the new breakers. A job well done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sue Meza","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgBrKXRHoNgE8x6L6iR0EINFFbPt209ZHlqEwjJ96MLhUiv4Tghg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The two guys that were here doing my generator install were timely, communicative, and respected our property. They cleaned up everything and made sure they communicated with me about what has been done. Now we’re just waiting for the city to do their inspection and they will get the generator hooked up to the gas line. I’m so happy that the next time it rains my sump pump will automatically come on even if there’s no power.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1uuTlslYxZ5uZ2q3ENQopeakKeGmQTFowqzuK-Kr80aOI_TY9rY4uSnNNCL4hDPLqqVQOIQyeY2tsPvtlHSsshveXM7-WoS0nR6PsgYvw_e5NMW0YxvAdNZt1Z6Q8IRqTlc1JH7ypRVg9D=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0oOLHkpPkyp3SMp0PucH09J_GnWIpSvfaSigAt77HuPxnaKxIy_OHw9QcB5N8Ze7pbThPLT1HVtf5HbWK-JPvR780slHJkFTPJhz12iXEuLHz_i3m__n_0PjZjJESrd3nCFYMCOKWDA7oI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Lq_oHuxPrWaxsptTOGTM1C1fit_lO3h84ZSrefymyOWnhufFWIwX